warrior myself so obviously biased. I would've thought either no buffs were allowed before duel start (i.e. if warrior had any cobalt or whatever, it couldn't be used prior to match start, enc could med to full but not buff/summon) or perhaps allow buffing/summoning, but once done the duel starts immediately, no medding to full afterwards.<br><br>Seems to me that in the rules used, the pure melees really get the rough end of the stick, other than being full hp they really have no need for a med period. Maybe this is less true for hybrids, I'm not sure.<br><br>So, I was just wondering what other people thought the rules should be for caster v melee dueling. Hell, even caster v caster... a wizard v a magician, should the magician be allowed to summon/buff a pet and himself right up then med to full?<br><br>I just basically want to see if it's just because I play a warrrior myself that this seems so unfair to me, so please post your opinions!  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13112">Mordi Tashkarii</a><br>Warlord<BR>Shadows of The Unseen<br>Devotee of The Tribunal<Br>Quellious Server<br><br>'I wish people would realize that there is no "god mode" in EQ. <br>Not only will you die, but you are expected to die. <br>In fact, Verant would prefer it if you died often.'</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uastalus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Astalus </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ukobservers.net/cwm/otn/blobs/ukliam2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MadCrazy Puller</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/14/01 4:26:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.homestead.com/chunli3/files/charlie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duels</span><hr size=1> I think they should be allowed to summon pet and get full mana for that if thats what their life is ie mage....however buffs and such should be when battle starts but that is my opinion...they would then have to decide nuke the war or buff the pet...uses more strategy <p><center<Br><b><img src="http://astalus.homestead.com/files/NEW-3.gif" ><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=557">Astalus Sath</a> <br> Monk of 44 Seasons</b><br> Quellious Server<br><a href=http://www.norrathfellowship.com><img src="http://astalus.homestead.com/files/title.jpg"width=200height=35</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/upaeg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paeg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.btinternet.com/~killspring/anmkilik.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/14/01 7:22:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duels</span><hr size=1> I don't agree with pre-fight buffing, but if it does take place, the caster should not be allowed to med to full and instead fight on with the mana they have remaining.  Or something. <p><image src="http://www.btinternet.com/~killspring/v8.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uishanserrasbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ishan Serrasbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All Your Base Are Belong To Us</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/14/01 11:04:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tvdance.com/jayandsilentbob/1a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duels</span><hr size=1> depends. i usually self-buff and med to full, and allow the same of my opponents.  As for the melee vs. pet class...i usually just ignore the pet and go straight to the source...rooting the pet if i must... <p><img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~ishan/ishansig4.gif" border="0"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/upalaziousfrydaddy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palazious Frydaddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/14/01 11:32:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duels</span><hr size=1> seems to be a common thread on PvP boards....<br><br>IMO...<br><br>Tanks strengths comes from weapons, armor etc.<br><br>Caster strength comes from spells, mana, pets etc.<br><br>Would it make someone proud to win a fight agains an oom caster who decided to pop a pet and buff himself?<br><br>no more than It would make a caster proud to win a fight against a tank who had to equip his armor and weapons before a fight.<br><br>I think both should be fully prepared for the fight.  Caster pets and buffs take a lot of mana and are designed to be used before the fight, whereas tanks wear their armor and weapons to the fight.<br><br>Maybe thats why before a raid on a particular mob all the pets are popped, buffs are given out, everyone meds to full, etc. BEFORE the fight.  If this were not intended then maybe Verant would call the raid party exploiting by preparing themselfs before killing a mob.<br><br>Good question tho and one that has many opinions.<br><br>To me a 60 warrior winning a duel with a 60 necro (1200 hp and 600 ac) who couldnt prepare would not be a fair fight.<br><br>But thats just my opinion.<br><br>Next part of this question usually is.. &quot;Is a caster using terrain to aid his fight cheating?&quot;<br><br>Pal<br>55 Evoker (still need to change the sig) <p><center><img src="http://www.cs.uidaho.edu/~meac9127/cs102/pallogo.gif" width="288" height="216"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uesmalyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Esmalyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/14/01 12:04:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duels</span><hr size=1> I don't think it's wrong at all for casters to buff themselves, med to full, haste a pet, or DS it. Yeah, casters are powerful but the right resist gear puts things in your favor. I wouldn't call it cheating. By now at one time or another we've come across VI's &quot;if you don't play my way, you could be banned&quot; tripe, so IMO I'm not surprised some people would question the fairness of full buff/med, or using other tactics like (at one time) Safe Fall to soften up a mob. I'd expect a rogue to take his/her sweet time poisoning not just 2 weapons, but every weapon s/he's carrying in their backpacks.<br><br>Then again, I think anyone dumb enough to challenge those weakling casters who call themselves enchanters to a duel deserve to be charmed and attack a guard. &gt;=) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uwhytspirit.showPublic