imes I think what's important are not the rules or the spirit of the rules, but who reviews a petition. I read a while back that they were going to stop monitoring abuses on PVP, including snaring druids while they pull. No, I don't think every wrong merits a drastic retaliation. It would be nice to get even with a player once in a while though, as long as it's not a habit.<br><br>Esmalyn's &quot;Donning flame-retardent suit&quot; Player <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ujurorb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JurorB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tall, Dark, and Hairy</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/14/01 2:01:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.kscable.com/mvandoren/gat1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duels</span><hr size=1> I have dueled with both my monk and my shaman so I can see both sides.  My monk's resist gear sucks so if I am fighting a caster around the same level who is allowed to prepare himself or herself fully, I stand no chance of winning.  It's not much fun to be charmed and made to attack mobs or NPCs, to be kited, to be stunned then nuked, or to be blinded and then killed by someone's pet.  On the other hand, I have fought duels as a shaman where I was not allowed to buff, summon a pet, cast DoTs, or med up.  Guess who won.<br><br>Now if it's just for fun or to experiment with a spell or ability, I don't really care.  If it's a competition, I like to see some consideration given to level and class differences.  Some